One Big Idea I'd Like to Add

I want to borrow one more concept from Framework—not just repairability, but repairability by design.

Let's make this an official engineering requirement:

No component should become inaccessible because of another unrelated component.

Examples:

You shouldn't have to remove the display to replace the battery.
You shouldn't have to remove the battery to replace a button if it can be avoided.
You shouldn't have to remove the DAC to access the USB-C board.

This will influence how we arrange the internals from day one. It might make the enclosure a few millimeters thicker, but it'll make the device dramatically easier to repair and upgrade. I think that's a tradeoff worth making, and it fits perfectly with the vision we've been building.
